Node.js User Management App
This is a simple Node.js application for managing users. It allows users to add new users via a form, view a list of existing users, and display a welcome message.

Features
Display a welcome message on the home page
Add new users via a form
Store user information in a text file
View a list of existing users
Redirect to the create user form if no users exist

##Requirements - install Nodejs - install nodemon - install express - install body-parser

## Installation

1. Clone the repository:
   https://github.com/prabha2612/Node_assign2.git

2. Navigate to the project directory:
   cd ASSIGN2

3. Install dependencies:
   npm install

## Usage

1. Start the server:
   node app.js

2. Open a web browser and navigate to `http://localhost:3000`.

3. You can now create users by visiting `/create` and listing users by visiting `/users`.

## File Structure

- `app.js`: Main entry point of the application.
- `routes.js`: Contains request handling logic. Defines routes for creating users, adding users, and listing users.
- `users.txt`: Text file to store user data.
